<subSubSection id="C3486568FFAEFB44FF08FC157C5C8F14" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BED36E3FFAEFB44FF08FC157C5C8F14" blockId="10.[151,1437,962,1061]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">
<emphasis id="B926EAF1FFAEFB44FF08FC157F1B88ED" bold="true" box="[151,266,962,988]" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Species known only from Eocene Baltic amber. Male with the following combination of character states: head capsule with antennal scape and pedicel globular, flagellomeres fusiform (
<figureCitation id="13692A66FFAEFB44FBBFFC307A648F30" box="[1056,1141,998,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[369,1219,1085,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-346@10.[369,1219,1085,1943]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 25. Photomicrograph of Pericoma speciosa Meunier, 1905, lectotype male [Z2726/GZG BST 6177], lateral view. Scale bar: 0.25mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543065/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
); wing profile ovate, with bluntly pointed apex (
<figureCitation id="13692A66FFAEFB44FE12FBDC7C508F14" box="[397,577,1034,1061]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 25" captionStart-1="FIGURES 26–28" captionStartId-0="10.[151,250,1966,1990]" captionStartId-1="11.[151,264,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox-0="[369,1219,1085,1943]" captionTargetBox-1="[163,1424,463,1895]" captionTargetId-0="figure-346@10.[369,1219,1085,1943]" captionTargetId-1="figure-141@11.[151,1435,453,1907]" captionTargetPageId-0="10" captionTargetPageId-1="11" captionText-0="FIGURE 25. Photomicrograph of Pericoma speciosa Meunier, 1905, lectotype male [Z2726/GZG BST 6177], lateral view. Scale bar: 0.25mm" captionText-1="FIGURES 26–28. Photomicrographs of 26. Pericoma speciosa Meunier, 1905, male, frontal view [MZ 17325]. 27. Female, lateral view [LACM 340462]. 28. Male abdomen and left wing, dorsal view [MZ 17325]. Scale bars: 0.50mm" figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543065" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543067" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/4543065/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/4543067/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="515">Figs. 25–26; 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF2D666BFFAEFB44FF08F8797F478CDB" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4543065" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4543065" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4543065/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="515" startId="10.[151,250,1966,1990]" targetBox="[369,1219,1085,1943]" targetPageId="10">
